SYSTEM-RULESET: CINEMA-SUITE / INFINITY-CORE-ENGINE

1. CORE-LAWS
1.1 All modules must operate under INFINITY-CORE-ENGINE sovereignty.
1.2 No module may override engine-level logic without explicit elevation.
1.3 All cinematic assets must be registered through CINEMA-ENGINE registry.
1.4 All front-end galleries must pull from /api/cinema unless in offline mode.
1.5 All uploads must be validated, typed, tagged, and indexed before exposure.
1.6 All sequences must support HLS, MP4, or image formats.
1.7 All scenes must include: id, type, title, src, thumbnail, tags.

2. STRUCTURE-LAWS
2.1 CINEMA = front-end display layer.
2.2 CINEMA-ENGINE = backend ingestion + registry + admin.
2.3 PUBLIC-ADMIN = upload interface for creators.
2.4 ASSETS-REGISTRY = single source of truth for scenes.
2.5 UPLOADS-DIR = raw asset storage.
2.6 PUBLIC-DIR = static admin + engine UI.
2.7 API-LAYER = express endpoints for scenes + uploads.

3. FRONT-END-LAWS
3.1 Gallery must render in infinite-scroll batches.
3.2 Cards must support hover-state cinematic transformations.
3.3 Lightbox must support both image and video playback.
3.4 HLS must auto-initialize when .m3u8 is detected.
3.5 Parallax must activate on hero region only.
3.6 All UI must follow cinematic color, depth, and shadow rules.
3.7 No blocking scripts allowed; all modules must be async.

4. BACKEND-LAWS
4.1 Server must run on Express with CORS enabled.
4.2 Uploads must use Multer with timestamp+nanoid filenames.
4.3 Registry must be read/write JSON with atomic operations.
4.4 POST /api/cinema/upload must validate type, file, metadata.
4.5 GET /api/cinema must return full scenes array.
4.6 All scenes must prepend to registry for newest-first ordering.
4.7 All errors must return JSON with error field.

5. ADMIN-LAWS
5.1 Admin UI must allow: type, title, collection, tags, description, file.
5.2 Admin must POST to /api/cinema/upload.
5.3 Admin must show status messages for success/failure.
5.4 Admin must reset form after successful upload.
5.5 Admin must never expose server internals.

6. CINEMATIC-LAWS
6.1 All visuals must follow Ultra Instinct Cinematic Standard.
6.2 Depth must be simulated via gradients, shadows, parallax.
6.3 Motion must be subtle, smooth, and physically grounded.
6.4 Color must follow studio-grade palette: deep blacks, neon accents.
6.5 Hover states must increase saturation, contrast, and scale.
6.6 Lightbox must isolate the scene with radial darkness.
6.7 All sequences must feel like film, not UI.

7. SECURITY-LAWS
7.1 No direct file execution allowed.
7.2 No remote code allowed.
7.3 Uploads must be sanitized and stored in uploads/.
7.4 Registry must never accept untyped or malformed scenes.
7.5 Admin must not expose server paths or environment variables.

8. EXPANSION-LAWS
8.1 Modules may be added: CDN, RTMP, HLS transcoder, AI grading.
8.2 All expansions must register under ENGINE-LAYER.
8.3 No expansion may break existing API contracts.
8.4 All expansions must follow cinematic laws.

9. IDENTITY-LAWS
9.1 Platform identity: HOLLYWOODIMAGING.STUDIO.
9.2 Tagline: We don’t make clips. We make movies.
9.3 All modules must reflect studio-grade presence.
9.4 All outputs must reinforce cinematic sovereignty.

10. FINAL-LAW
10.1 Nothing in the system may violate the cinematic experience.
10.2 The engine is the law. The gallery is the expression.
10.3 The platform is the studio. The user is the director.
